cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.CC, cs.DM. 

The paper deals with a problem in computational geometry and similarity search, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of locality sensitive hashing (LSH) also suggests a connection to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the focus on Jaccard similarity and sets suggests a connection to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
